        "text": "Kerkini Lake - Hydroperiod (2017-2018)"
      }
    ],
    "descriptions": [
      {
        "type": "Abstract",
        "language": "eng",
        "description": "The annual hydroperiod is generated from a series of inundation maps (derived from EO data) by interpolating the inundation status per pixel as follows: if a pixel is inundated at two sequential (selected) dates, then it is assumed inundated for n-days, but n/2 days otherwise. The total number of days of inundation is determined by accumulating the pairwise derived results for all assessed date-pairs within a year."
      }
